ch als die Fortschreibung und Ausformulierung eines Grundgedankens von Aristoteles' politischer Philosophie begriffen werden sollte, nicht als radikaler Bruch mit ihr.   aWhat does Aristotle regard as the conditions of a legitimate relationship between political rule and the law? The interpretation of Aristotelian politics in this study shows that the central political project of the modern age – namely, the grounding and implementation of the natural rights of the individual – can be conceptualized as the continuation and embodiment of Aristotle’s political philosophy rather than a radical break from it.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jun 2020) 0aCivil rights. 0aNatural law. 4aAntike. 4aAntiquit. 4aIndividuality. 4aIndividualität. 4aModerne. 4aModernity. 4aPolitics. 4aPolitik. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2015z978311070098508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2015z9783110439687oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2015z9783110438680oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831103872230 cprintz978311037579440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311037585540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110375855423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110375855.jpg  a978-3-11-070098-5  DG Plus eBook-Package 2015b2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2015  aZDB-23-DPHb2015